        <h3 class="margin">My Story</h3>
        <p>Welcome to my website! My name is Trisha and I’m an Occupational Therapist. I have been in practice since 2006, working primarily within the pediatric population, doing Early Intervention via Regional Centers and CCS Medical Therapy Program with individuals from 0-21 years old.  I was born and raised in San Francisco, CA until 9 years old, when my mother moved us to Los Angeles, specifically West Hollywood, where many of my adolescent and teenage experiences helped mold me into the person I am today. I was raised by an amazing single mother, who provided an environment of unconditional love, diversity, empathy, and compassion that I carried forward into my adulthood, not only as a proud mother to my son Miles, but also in my role as an occupational therapist, trusted friend, and strong woman warrior. Most important to me is the impact I have on my son and the future I help secure for him. It is through his eyes and experiences that drives me to do what I do, and fight for what I believe is precious and right. </p>
